Date when first case in each first-level administration was reported

This article documents the chronology and epidemiology of SARS-CoV-2 in March 2020, the virus which causes the coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) and is responsible for the COVID-19 pandemic. The first human cases of COVID-19 were identified in Wuhan, Hubei, China, in December 2019.

Case statistics

Further information: Timeline of the COVID-19 pandemic § Case statistics

Pandemic chronology

1 March

WHO Situation Report 41:[1]

Map of the WHO's regional offices and their respective operating regions.
  Africa; HQ: Brazzaville, Republic of the Congo
  Western Pacific; HQ: Manila, Philippines
  Eastern Mediterranean; HQ: Cairo, Egypt
  South East Asia; HQ: New Delhi, India
  Europe; HQ: Copenhagen, Denmark
  Americas; HQ: Washington, D.C., US
  • Armenia confirmed its first case, a 29-year-old man returning from Iran.[2]
  • Australia confirmed the first death in the country, a 78-year-old man from the cruise ship Diamond Princess.[3] One additional case was confirmed, bringing the total number to 26.[4]
  • Austria confirmed four more cases, bringing the total number to 14.[5]
  • Bahrain confirmed six more cases, bringing the total number to 47.[6]
  • Canada confirmed four new cases in Ontario, bringing the total number to 24. All four had travel history to Iran or Egypt.[7][8]
  • China confirmed 573 new cases; 570 of which were in Hubei province, bringing the total number to 79,824. Deaths increased by 35 to a total of 2,870.[9]
  • The Czech Republic confirmed the first three cases in the country, individuals that had traveled from Northern Italy.[10]
  • The Dominican Republic confirmed its first case, a 62-year-old Italian tourist.[11]
  • Ecuador confirmed five more cases, bringing the total to six.[12][13]
  • Egypt confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to two.[14]
  • Finland confirmed two more cases related to a woman diagnosed on 27 February, bringing the total number to six.[15]
  • France confirmed 30 more cases, bringing the total number to 130.[16]
  • Germany confirmed 63 more cases, bringing the total number to 129.[17]
  • Hong Kong confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 98.[18]
  • Iran confirmed 385 new cases with 11 more deaths, bringing the total number to 978 and 54, respectively.[19] A total of 23 members of Parliament of Iran, about 8%, had tested positive for the virus.[20]
  • Iraq confirmed six more cases, bringing the total number to 19.[21]
  • Israel confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 10.[22]
  • Italy confirmed 566 new cases and five deaths, bringing the total number to 1,694 and 34, respectively.[23]
  • Japan confirmed another death from the coronavirus, bringing the total to six.[24]
  • Malaysia confirmed four more cases, bringing the total number to 29.[25]
  • Mexico confirmed one additional case, bringing the total number to five.[26]
  • The Netherlands confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 10.[27]
  • Saint Barthélemy confirmed its first case.[28]
  • Saint Martin confirmed its first case.[28]
  • San Marino confirmed seven more cases, bringing the total number to eight. The first death was also confirmed.[29]
  • Scotland confirmed its first case.[30]
  • Singapore confirmed four more cases, bringing the total number to 106.[31]
  • South Korea confirmed 376 more cases, bringing the total number to 3,526. Another 210 cases were later confirmed with the 18th death reported, bringing the total number to 3,736.[32]
  • Spain confirmed 26 more cases, bringing the total number to 84.[33] Spain also confirmed its first death due to the outbreak, in Valencia.[34]
  • Sweden confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to 14.[35]
  • Thailand confirmed its first death from the coronavirus, a 35-year-old retail worker who also had dengue fever.[36]
  • The United Kingdom confirmed an additional 13 cases of the virus, including one person from Essex who had not traveled to any country previously affected by the virus, bringing the total in the country to 35.[37]
  • The United States reported the second confirmed death in Washington state. The first cases in Rhode Island, Florida, and New York were confirmed. The authorities confirmed 21 more cases in total, bringing the number to 89.[38][39]

2 March

WHO Situation Report 42:[40]

  • Andorra confirmed its first case.[41]
  • Australia confirmed four new cases, bringing the total number to 30, including its first human-to-human transmission.[42]
  • Bahrain confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 49.[43]
  • Canada confirmed three more cases, all in Ontario, bringing the total number to 27.[44][45]
  • China confirmed 202 new cases, bringing the total number to 80,026. Deaths increased by 42 to a total of 2,912.[46]
  • France confirmed 61 more cases, bringing the total number to 191. The third death was also reported.[47]
  • Germany confirmed 21 more cases, bringing the total number to 150.[48]
  • India reported its first cases since the initial outbreak. One case was detected in New Delhi, while the other was from Telangana. Another confirmed case was later detected in Jaipur, bringing the total number to six.[49][50]
  • Indonesian president Joko Widodo announced the first two confirmed cases in the country.[51] The two people contracted the virus from a Japanese individual in Depok, who later tested positive in Malaysia. The mother and daughter are now hospitalized in North Jakarta.[52][53]
  • Iran's total cases rose to 1,501 with 66 deaths.[54]
  • Iraq confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 21.[55]
  • Ireland Tourism authorities announced that one of the largest annual events, the 2020 Dublin St Patricks Day Parade, was canceled.[56]
  • Israel confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 12.[57]
  • Italy confirmed 342 new cases and 18 deaths, bringing the total number to 2,064 and 52, respectively.[58]
  • Jordan confirmed its first case.[59]
  • Kuwait confirmed 10 more cases, bringing the total number to 56.[60]
  • Latvia confirmed its first case, a woman who had flown from Milan to Riga through Munich.[61]
  • Morocco confirmed its first case.[62]
  • The Netherlands confirmed eight new cases, bringing the total number to 18.[63]
  • Portugal confirmed its first two cases, one of whom had returned from Italy, the other from Spain.[64]
  • Qatar confirmed four new cases, taking their total to seven.[65]
  • Russia confirmed one additional case, bringing the total to six cases.[66]
  • Saudi Arabia confirmed their first case in a citizen who had traveled to Iran and returned to Saudi Arabia via Bahrain.[67]
  • Senegal confirmed its first case, where the person had recently traveled from France.[68]
  • Singapore confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 108.[69]
  • South Korea confirmed 476 more cases, bringing the total number to 4,212. Four more deaths were confirmed, bringing the total to 22.[70] Another 123 cases were later confirmed, bringing the total number to 4,335.[71]
  • Spain confirmed 36 more cases, bringing the total number to 120.[72]
  • Sweden confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to 15.[73]
  • Taiwan confirmed one additional case, bringing the total to 41 cases.[74]
  • Thailand confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to 43.[75]
  • Tunisia confirmed its first case.[76]
  • The United Kingdom confirmed three additional cases, taking the total to 39. An original fourth diagnosis of positive of a person was confirmed later as negative.[77]
  • The United States confirmed 13 more cases, bringing the total number to 102. Five more deaths were also confirmed, bringing the total number to six.[78]

3 March

WHO Situation Report 43:[79]

  • Argentina confirmed its first case, a person who had recently returned from Italy.[80]
  • Australia confirmed eight more cases, bringing the total number to 38.[81]
  • Canada confirmed six more cases, two in Ontario and four in British Columbia, bringing the total to 33.[82][83][84]
  • Chile confirmed its first case.[85]
  • China confirmed 125 new cases, the lowest number of new cases since January, bringing the total number to 80,151. Also, 31 new deaths were confirmed, bringing the total to 2,943.[86]
  • Ecuador confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 10.
  • France confirmed 21 more cases, bringing the total number to 212. The fourth death was also reported.[87]
  • Germany confirmed 38 more cases, bringing the total number to 188.[88]
  • Gibraltar confirmed its first case, a person who had traveled back from Northern Italy via Malaga airport.[89]
  • Iran confirmed that 23 MPs were diagnosed with the virus.[90] The country confirmed 835 more cases with 11 more deaths, bringing the total number to 2,336 and 77, respectively.[91]
  • Ireland confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to two.[92]
  • Italy confirmed 466 new cases and 28 deaths, bringing the total number to 2,502 and 80, respectively.[93]
  • Liechtenstein confirmed its first case.[94]
  • Malaysia confirmed seven more cases, bringing the total number to 36.[95]
  • San Marino confirmed two new cases, bringing the total number to 10.[96]
  • Singapore confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 110.[97]
  • South Korea confirmed 600 more cases, bringing the total number to 4,812. Also, 12 more deaths were confirmed, bringing the total to 34.[98] In the afternoon, 377 more cases were confirmed, along with two more deaths, taking the total to 5,186 cases and 36 deaths.[99]
  • Spain confirmed the first death in the country, a person who died on 13 February, making him the earliest recorded death in Europe.[100] The country reported 31 more cases, bringing the total number to 151.[101]
  • Sweden confirmed 15 more cases, bringing the total number to 30.[102]
  • Ukraine confirmed its first case, a person having traveled from Italy via Romania.[103]
  • The United Kingdom confirmed 12 new cases, bringing the total number to 51.[104]
  • The United States confirmed three more deaths, bringing the total to nine.[105] The first case of coronavirus in North Carolina was reported, coming from the nursing home in Washington state responsible for the first deaths from the virus.[106] Another case in Florida was presumptively confirmed positive, bringing the total number of Floridian cases to three.[107] The number of cases stood at 126, increasing by 24 from 102.

4 March

WHO Situation Report 44:[108]

  • Brazil confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to four.[109]
  • Canada confirmed one more case in British Columbia, bringing the total number to 34.[110]
  • China confirmed 119 new cases, bringing the total number to 80,270. 38 new deaths were also confirmed, bringing the total to 2,981.[111]
  • The Faroe Islands confirmed its first case.[112]
  • France confirmed 73 more cases, bringing the total number to 285.[113]
  • Germany confirmed 52 more cases, bringing the total number to 240.[114]
  • Hong Kong confirmed a case of human-to-animal transmission involving a pet dog.[115]
  • Hungary confirmed its first cases, two Iranian students who were asymptomatic.[116]
  • India confirmed 23 more cases, including 15 Italian tourists, bringing the total number to 29.[117][118]
  • Iraq confirmed its first death from the coronavirus.[119]
  • Italy confirmed 28 more deaths, bringing the total to 107. This made it the highest jump in a single day. The country confirmed 587 new cases, bringing the total number to 3,089.[120]
  • Cases in Japan had topped the 1,000 mark (including 706 cases on the cruise ship Diamond Princess which the World Health Organization classifies as being located "on an international conveyance" and not in Japan) with the first confirmed case in Yamaguchi prefecture.[121]
  • Malaysia confirmed 14 more cases, bringing the total number to 50.[122]
  • New Zealand confirmed its second case of the coronavirus. The infected individual had returned the previous week from Italy with her family on an Air New Zealand flight from Singapore to Auckland.[123]
  • Poland confirmed its first case.[124][non-primary source needed]
  • San Marino confirmed five more cases, bringing the total number to 15.[125]
  • Singapore confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to 112.[126]
  • Slovenia confirmed its first case, a person who had traveled through Italy.[127]
  • South Korea confirmed 516 more cases, bringing the total number to 5,328.[128] Another 293 cases were confirmed in the afternoon, bringing the total number to 5,621.[129]
  • Sweden confirmed 22 more cases, bringing the total number to 52.[130]
  • The United Kingdom confirmed 34 new cases, then Northern Ireland confirmed an additional two, bringing the total number to 87.[131]
  • The United States confirmed 11 total deaths, with the first death outside of Washington state in California. California's total of infections had jumped to 51.[132] The country confirmed 33 new cases, bringing the total number to 159.

5 March

WHO Situation Report 45:[133]

  • Algeria confirmed nine additional cases, bringing the total number to 17.[134]
  • Belgium confirmed 27 new cases, bringing the total number to 50.[135]
  • Brazil confirmed three new cases, bringing the total to eight.[136]
  • Bosnia and Herzegovina confirmed the first two cases in the country.[137]
  • Canada confirmed 14 new cases three in Ontario, two in Quebec, and the first one in Alberta, bringing the total to 48.[138][139],[140]
  • China confirmed 139 new cases, bringing the total number to 80,409. Also, 31 new deaths were confirmed (all in Hubei), bringing the total to 3,012.[141]
  • Ecuador confirmed three more cases, bringing the total number to 13.[142]
  • Egypt confirmed the first case in an Egyptian national, who had recently traveled from Serbia via France.[143]
  • France registered 92 new confirmed cases, taking the total number of cases to 377. It also saw deaths rise from four to six.[144] This then rose to 423 total cases and seven deaths.[145] Jean-Luc Reitzer was the first Assembly member to be diagnosed with the virus.[146]
  • Georgia confirmed five new cases, all of whom had recently returned from Italy.[147]
  • Germany confirmed 87 new cases, taking it to a total of 349.[148]
  • Greece confirmed its 10th case.[149] It later confirmed an additional 21 cases, taking it to a total of 31.[150]
  • India confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to 30.[151]
  • Iran saw its largest daily increase in cases, with 591 new cases, taking it to a total of 3,513 confirmed cases. It also saw 15 new deaths, increasing its total to 107.[152][non-primary source needed] Hossein Sheikholeslam, a diplomat, former member of parliament, and Iran's former ambassador to Syria, died from the virus.[153][non-primary source needed]
  • Ireland confirmed six new cases, bringing the total number to 13.[154][non-primary source needed]
  • Israel confirmed two new cases, bringing the total to 17. And of these was a bus driver from East Jerusalem who drove a group of Greek tourists in Israel and the West Bank, the other having recently returned from Italy.[155]
  • Italy reported 769 new cases and 41 new deaths, bringing the total number to 3,850 and 148, respectively.[156]
  • Malaysia confirmed five more cases, bringing the total number to 55.[157]
  • Martinique confirmed its first two cases.[158]
  • The Netherlands confirmed 44 new cases, bringing the total number to 82.[159]
  • New Zealand confirmed its third case, an Auckland man who had contracted the virus after family members had returned from a trip to Iran. Relatives of the man at two Auckland schools, Auckland Grammar School and Ormiston Junior College, had also been placed into isolation.[160][161]
  • Norway confirmed six new cases, bringing the total number to 66.[162]
  • Pakistan confirmed a sixth case, a 69-year-old man in Karachi.[163]
  • Palestine reported its first cases in the West Bank city of Bethlehem. Seven staff at a hotel were reported to be infected by visiting tourists from Greece.[164] These tourists were the same ones who the Israeli bus driver was infected from.[155]
  • Russia confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to seven.[165]
  • Saudi Arabia confirmed three additional cases, bringing the total number to five.[166][non-primary source needed]
  • Scotland confirmed three more cases, bringing the total to six.[167]
  • Singapore confirmed five more cases, bringing the total number to 117.[168]
  • South Africa records its first case in the KwaZulu-Natal province.[169]
  • South Korea confirmed 145 more cases, bringing the total number to 5,766. The death toll had reached 35.[170] Another 322 more cases and six more deaths are confirmed later in the afternoon, bringing the total to 6,088 cases and 41 deaths, respectively.[171]
  • Spain had confirmed that the total number of cases had risen to 234.[172]
  • Sweden confirmed 42 more cases, bringing the total number to 94.[173]
  • Switzerland reported its first death from the virus.[174]
  • Thailand confirmed four new cases, bringing the total to 47.[175]
  • The United Kingdom's total increased to 90. The UK also later confirmed the total number of cases had increased further up to 116, as well as recording the first death in the country, an older person with underlying health conditions.[176]
  • One additional death in Washington state brought the US total to 12.[177] The United States saw a significant increase in cases, with 31 new cases in Washington state.[178] In New York state, cases doubled to 22.[179] Colorado's first two cases were confirmed.[180] In total, the US confirmed 69 more cases, bringing the total number to 228. Three more deaths were reported, bringing the total number to 14.[citation needed]

6 March

WHO Situation Report 46:[181]

  • Austria announced 13 new cases, taking its total to 55.[citation needed]
  • Belgium confirmed 59 new cases, bringing the total to 109.[182]
  • Bhutan announced its first case, an American tourist who had recently also traveled to India after leaving the United States on 18 February.[183][non-primary source needed][184]
  • Brazil confirmed five new cases, bringing the total number to 13.[185]
  • Cameroon confirmed its first case, a French citizen.[186][non-primary source needed]
  • Canada confirmed four new cases in Ontario, bringing the total to 51 with 26 from Ontario. A husband and wife returned from the cruise ship Grand Princess in California and two men returned from Iran and Las Vegas and then two more cases were confirmed later in Ontario, bringing the total to 53 and Alberta reported one new case bringing the total number to 54.[187][188][189]
  • China confirmed 143 new cases, bringing the total number to 80,552. Also, 30 new deaths were confirmed, bringing the total to 3,042. Hubei had no cases as a result.[190][191] In addition, the country detected four new cases in Beijing, all visiting Italian nationals.[192]
  • Colombia confirmed its first case, a woman who recently traveled from Italy.[193]
  • Costa Rica had confirmed its first case involving an American from New York.[194]
  • Egypt confirmed 12 additional cases, bringing the total number to 15.[195]
  • France confirmed 190 new cases and two additional deaths, bringing the total to 613 cases and nine deaths.[citation needed]
  • Germany confirmed 185 new cases, taking it to a total of 534.[196] Later, 105 more cases were confirmed, bringing the total number to 639.[197]
  • The cruise ship Grand Princess announced it had 21 people on board testing positive.[citation needed]
  • Greece confirmed 14 additional cases.[citation needed]
  • Iceland confirmed six additional cases, bringing the total to 43.[198]
  • India confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to 31.[199]
  • Indonesia confirmed two more cases, bringing the total number to four.
  • Iran confirmed 1,234 new cases and 16 new deaths, taking its totals up to 4,747 cases and 124 deaths. They also reported 913 people had recovered.[200][non-primary source needed]
  • Italy announced 778 new cases and 49 new deaths.[201]
  • Malaysia confirmed 28 new cases,[202] the largest daily increase in the country's number of confirmed cases. This took the country's total to 83.[203]
  • The Netherlands reported its first death, and 44 new cases, bringing it to a total of 128 cases.[204]
  • New Zealand confirmed its fourth case: a man who is the partner of the second case confirmed on 3 March.[205][206]
  • North Macedonia confirmed two additional cases, taking its total to three.[207]
  • Peru confirmed its first case.[208]
  • Poland confirmed four additional cases (two people that traveled from Italy, one person who traveled from United Kingdom, and one person who traveled from Germany with the first case confirmed a day earlier), taking their total to five.[209][non-primary source needed]
  • Portugal confirmed four additional cases (three in Porto and one in Lisbon), bringing the total to 13. All three cases in Porto had a connection with Italy.[210][211]
  • Qatar confirmed three new cases, taking it to a total of 11.[212]
  • Russia confirmed six more cases, bringing the total number to 13.[213]
  • Serbia confirmed its first case.[214]
  • Singapore confirmed 13 new cases, bringing the total number to 130. This was the largest increase of cases in a single day so far.[215]
  • Slovakia confirmed its first case.[216]
  • South Korea confirmed 196 more cases, bringing the total number to 6,284. One more death was confirmed, bringing the total to 42.[217] Another 309 cases and another death were later confirmed, bringing the total to 6,593 and 43 respectively.[218]
  • Spain confirmed 104 additional cases, bringing the total number to 360.
  • Sweden confirmed 43 additional cases, bringing the total number to 137.[219]
  • Switzerland announced 123 additional cases, raising it to a total of 210 cases and one death.
  • Thailand confirmed one new case, bringing the total to 48.[220]
  • Togo confirmed its first case.[221]
  • In the United Kingdom, the total number of cases were confirmed as 163, a rise of 47 and the highest day-on-day increase.[222]
  • In the United States, the first three cases were confirmed in the state of Maryland.[223] Two deaths in Florida were confirmed.[224] Officials in the US state of Hawaii had confirmed their first case, a former passenger of the cruise ship Grand Princess.[225] In total, the US confirmed 104 more cases, bringing the total number to 332. One more death in Washington State plus two in Florida brought the total number of US deaths to 17.[226][227] In California, a Santa Clara County resident died at home, whose death was attributed later in April to COVID-19.[228] The WHO has different data though, with 19 new cases, totaling to 148, and one new death, totaling to 10.[181]
  • Vatican City confirmed its first case.[229]
  • Vietnam confirmed one more case, bringing the total number to 17. It was the first case in three weeks.[230]

7 March

WHO Situation Report 47:[231]

  • Afghanistan confirmed three additional cases, taking the total to four.[232]
  • Argentina confirmed its first death, also the first in South America, a 64-year-old man who had traveled to Paris.[233]
  • Bahrain confirmed 19 new cases, taking the total number to 79.[234]
  • Belgium confirmed 60 additional cases, bringing the total number to 169.[235]
  • Brazil confirmed six new cases of COVID-19, raising the total number to 19.[236]
  • Canada confirmed six additional cases, taking the total to 60.[237]
  • China confirmed 99 new cases, bringing the total number to 80,651. Deaths increased by 28 to a total of 3,070.[238]
  • Egypt confirmed 33 new cases on a Nile cruise ship.[239]
  • France's total rose to 949 cases and 16 deaths.[240]
  • Germany confirmed 45 new cases, taking it to a total of 684.[241] Another 116 cases were later confirmed, bringing the total number to 800.[242]
  • Iran confirmed 1,076 new cases and 21 additional deaths, taking it to a total of 5,823 infected and 145 dead. They also confirmed 16,000 cases were hospitalized as suspect cases and 1,669 cases had recovered.[243] Another MP, Fatemeh Rahbar, died. She had recently been elected to the parliament.[244]
  • Iraq confirmed eight new cases, taking the total to 46.[245]
  • Italy confirmed 1,247 new cases and 36 new deaths.[citation needed]
  • Maldives confirmed its first cases, two overseas hotel employees.[246]
  • Malaysia confirmed 10 more new cases, bringing the total number to 93.[247]
  • Malta reported its first three cases, an Italian family who were residents in Malta. They had gone on holiday to Northern Italy and had been in self-quarantine before being tested for the coronavirus. They were now in isolation at Mater Dei Hospital.[248]
  • Moldova confirmed its first case, a person taken to hospital after arriving on a flight from Italy.[249]
  • New Zealand confirmed its fifth case of the coronavirus: a woman who was the partner of the third COVID-19 case confirmed in New Zealand.[250]
  • Palestine confirmed 22 cases.[251]
  • Paraguay confirmed its first case.[citation needed]
  • Peru confirmed five more cases, bringing the total to six.[252]
  • Poland confirmed an additional case, bringing the total to six.[253][non-primary source needed]
  • Singapore confirmed eight more cases, bringing the total number to 138.[254]
  • South Korea confirmed 174 more cases and one more death, bringing the total number to 6,767 and 44, respectively.[255] Another 274 new cases and four new deaths were later confirmed, taking the total to 7,041 and 48, respectively.[256]
  • Spain confirmed 70 new cases and two deaths. The total number of cases was now 516 cases.[257]
  • Thailand confirmed two new cases, bringing the total to 50.[258]
  • The United Arab Emirates confirmed 15 additional cases, taking its total to 45.[259]

Notably, residents would be allowed to leave solely for going to the grocery store, pharmacy, for a medical appointment, or for exercise with a maximum 2 km (1.2 mi) radius from their house where social distancing must be practised and exercise time must be kept short.[969]

  • Panama confirmed 112 new cases, bringing the total to 786, and confirmed five new deaths, bringing the total to 14.[976]
  • Singapore confirmed 49 new cases, bringing the total number to 732.[977]
  • South Africa confirmed its first death at the same time as when the lockdown in the country began.[978]
  • South Korea confirmed 91 new cases and eight new deaths, bringing the total to 9,332 and 139, respectively.[979]
  • Spain recorded the highest single-day death toll worldwide to date, with 769 deaths. There were now 64,059 confirmed cases, up from 56,188.[980]
  • The United States confirmed at least 101,242 cases based on figures collated by Johns Hopkins University, overtaking China (81,782) and Italy (80,589). The US death toll surpassed 1,500.[981][982]
  • News reports citing a government document reported that a 57-year-old woman, who tested positive for the coronavirus disease on 10 December 2019 and was described in The Wall Street Journal on 6 March 2020, may have been patient zero in the coronavirus pandemic.[983][984]
  • The first oil refinery shutdowns in India and Europe were announced while global refinery runs dropped in response to plunging demand as countries worldwide implemented lockdowns.[985]

28 March

WHO Situation Report 68:[986]

  • In Canada, the province of Ontario had reported 151 new cases and one new death.[987][988] Furthermore, the province of Quebec had reported 477 new cases.[968]
  • Ireland confirmed 294 new cases and 14 deaths, the largest death toll to date. This gave a total of 2,415 confirmed cases and 36 deaths.[989]
  • Italy surpassed 10,000 deaths attributed to the virus.[990]
  • Malaysia confirmed a new death, bringing the total to 27. There were also 159 new cases confirmed, bringing the total number to 2,320.[991]
  • New Zealand reported 83 new cases including 78 confirmed and five probable cases, bringing the total to 451.[992]
  • Palestine confirmed six new cases, bringing the total to 97.[993]
  • Panama confirmed 115 new cases, bringing the total to 901, and confirmed three new deaths, bringing the total to 17.[994]
  • Singapore confirmed 70 new cases, bringing the total number to 802.[995]
  • South Korea confirmed 146 new cases and five new deaths, bringing the total to 9,478 and 144, respectively.[996]
  • The United Kingdom confirmed that positive test results had risen to 17,089 and there had been 260 new deaths, increasing the total to 1,019.[997][non-primary source needed]

29 March

WHO Situation Report 69:[998]

  • In Canada, the province of Ontario had reported a new record high of 211 new cases and four new deaths.[999][1000] Furthermore, the province of Quebec had reported 342 new cases.[1001]
  • Ireland confirmed 200 new cases and 10 deaths. This gives a total of 2,615 confirmed cases and 46 deaths.[1002]
  • Israel reported 628 new cases, bringing the total to 4,247. The country also reported three new deaths, bring the total number to 15.[1003]
  • Malaysia reported seven new deaths, bringing the total to 34. The country also confirmed 150 new cases, bringing the total number to 2,470.[1004][1005]
  • New Zealand reported 60 new confirmed and 3 new probable cases, bringing the total number of confirmed and probable cases to 514. The country also recorded its first death.[1006][1007]
  • Palestine confirms nine new cases, bringing the total to 108.[1008][1009]
  • Panama confirmed 88 new cases, bringing the total to 989, and confirmed seven new deaths, bringing the total to 24.[1010]
  • Singapore confirmed its third death.[1011] At the same time, 42 new cases were confirmed, bringing the total to 844.[1012]
  • South Korea confirmed 105 new cases and eight new deaths, bringing the total to 9,583 and 152, respectively.[1013]

30 March

WHO Situation Report 70:[1014]

  • Botswana recorded its first three cases.[1015]
  • In Canada, the province of Ontario had reported a new record high of 351 new cases and 10 new deaths.[1016][1017] Furthermore, the province of Quebec had reporting 590 new cases.[1018]
  • France reported 418 deaths in the past 24 hours, bringing the total number of fatalities to 3,024. France has 44,550 confirmed cases.[1019]
  • Iran confirmed 2,757 official deaths, with more than 40,000 confirmed cases.[1019]
  • Ireland confirmed 295 new cases and eight deaths. This gave a total of 2,910 confirmed cases and 54 deaths.[1020]
  • Malaysia reported three new deaths, bringing the total to 37. The country also confirmed 156 new cases, bringing the total number to 2,626.[1021]
  • New Zealand reported 76 new cases, bringing the total number of confirmed and probable cases to 589.[1022][1023]
  • Palestine confirmed seven new cases, bringing the total number of cases to 115.[1024]
  • Panama confirmed 86 new cases, bringing the total to 1,075, and reported 27 deaths so far.[1025]
  • Singapore confirmed 35 new cases, bringing the total number to 879.[1026]
  • South Korea confirmed 78 new cases and six new deaths, bringing the total to 9,661 and 158, respectively.[1027]
  • Spain reported that 812 people have died from the coronavirus in the period between Sunday and Monday.[1028]
  • In the United States, New York's official death toll exceeded 1,000.[1019]

31 March

WHO Situation Report 71:[1029]

  • Burundi confirmed its first two cases.[1030]
  • In Canada, the province of Ontario had reported 260 new cases and no new deaths.[1031][1032] Furthermore, the province of Quebec had reported 732 new cases.[1033]
  • China reported 48 new confirmed "imported cases" of the coronavirus but no new domestically transmitted cases on 30 March.[1034]
  • Guam confirmed two new cases, bringing the total number to 58.[1035]
  • Ireland confirmed 325 new cases, the most to date, and 17 deaths, the most to date. This gave a total of 3,235 confirmed cases and 71 deaths.[1036]
  • Malaysia reported six new deaths, bringing the total death toll to 43. In addition, 140 new cases were confirmed, bringing the total number to 2,766.[1037]
  • New Zealand confirmed 58 new confirmed and probable cases, bringing the total number to 647, with 74 people having recovered.[1038][1039]
  • Palestine confirmed two new cases, bringing the total to 117 including 10 in Gaza.[1040]
  • Panama confirmed 106 new cases, bringing the total to 1,181, and reported three new deaths, bringing the total to 30.[1041]
  • Sierra Leone confirmed its first case.[1042]
  • Singapore confirmed 47 new cases, bringing the total number to 926.[1043]
  • Sint Eustatius confirmed its first two cases.[1044][1045]
  • Somaliland confirmed its first two cases.[1046]
  • South Korea confirmed 125 new cases and four new deaths, bringing the total to 9,786 and 162, respectively.[1047]
  • The captain of a US Navy aircraft carrier USS Theodore Roosevelt that had more than 100 cases of coronavirus wrote a stunning plea for help to senior military officials.[1048]
